SKATES v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [H. C. No. 6,

September Term, 1958.]

Decided January 19, 1959.

Before Beune, C. J., and Hendeeson, Hammond, Peescott and Hoeney, JJ.

Pee Cueiam.

This is the petitioner’s second application for leave to appeal from the denial of a writ of habeas corpus. His previous application was considered in Skates v. Warden, 214 Md. 639.

His application herein is denied for the reasons, fully and ably, set forth by Judge Michaelson in the court below.

Application denied, with costs.
